insta: pumpkin.pixie.princess</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gB00oKB</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[pumpkinpixieprincess]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Pain au chocolate</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/NidiokF</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HY3xd3z.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/NidiokF</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[370zSteve]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Just A Girl &amp; Her Cat</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/mcEGDK6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/BOJ41Ez.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/mcEGDK6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Devi8tor]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/S9YjvP4</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/MmoiLNC.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/S9YjvP4</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[lifonaut]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Current tranformation journey</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/qdpegzr</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/zvz6EAt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>5 years and about 70lbs between pictures.  Slowly but surely the progress is coming.  Each week, I notice new "cuts" as I look in the mirror.  Because I have started a recomposition journey, the scale has become somewhat of a frustration for me because I am still learning to change my mindset from losing weight to losing fat.   The pictures and quick mirror glances have been a new source of encouragement in my journey.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/qdpegzr</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mikey32935]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The Idiots of Imgur: A Mini Dump pt 51</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/Bo2DMZK</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2eRpbYM.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OasNp2C.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Q1pOSwY.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/qQclxTq.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tI2PZUY.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1l9MvIa.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/JEzPHyC.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kU9J05v.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/2yiBt9E.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Bz03FD5.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/Bo2DMZK</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[UncleSlam123]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Last round of chemo!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/IU68nnP</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/XC6HU9E.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>7 months off work, 6 months of chemo, and I’m finally on my last treatment! IV today then 2 weeks of chemo pills, so technically today is just the beginning of the end. 

I don’t get another scan for a couple months, so I’ll continue to keep my fingers crossed that this is the end of treatments. If anyone is willing to send positive vibes I’ll take ‘em! 

I’d like to say that this has changed my whole outlook, but truly I just can’t wait to get back to my normal life the best I can. Maybe that means I’m just incredibly lucky to have a life I was already happy with! My husband, family, friends, and kitties have all been amazing support and I can’t thank them enough. And thank you to the imgur community for keeping me entertained!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/WVtrU2s.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Cat tax. My 2 babies Sookie and Neville                                                *edit* WOW! Front page and SO much support from my imgur family! You’re all so wonderful—thank you for celebrating with me. Cute story: due to Covid I can’t have anyone in treatments with me, so when I got into the car with my husband he had our families on FaceTime and a bell for me to ring! I have an amazing hubby!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/IU68nnP</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[casiehansolo]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Day 305: of cheeseburgers I want inside of me</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/C5qwZ1M</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ySDyXDR.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Brie + Fig

